  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nWhen the slide button is redrawn, it shows a flicker that moves the text inside it to the right.\r\n\r\nThis is due to the `track-width` ratom that is set in an `on-layout`  callback. The component is placed in the namespace \r\n`quo.components.buttons.slide-button.view`\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nRemove the flickering\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nFlickers when it's rerendered.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1.  Go to Quo2 preview components\r\n2. Buttons -> slide-button\r\n3. Press the `blur?` boolean, now the text, when the component is rerendered will be moved to the right \r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
